A 24-wheeler truck ploughed into a house on the corner of Linwood and Waverleydale, Pietermaritzburg, on Wednesday. According to a police source, a 24-wheeler truck is suspected to have lost its brakes coming down Sweetwaters Road, going into Linwood drive and ploughing into a wall. “The driver and passenger were slightly injured and there were no fatalities,” said the source. SAPS is said to be conducting further investigations.